The paper focuses on road damage detection using deep neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning models also suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) being a relevant sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for a uniform dataset and the potential applications of the system, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-categories.
